        <section>
            <h1>About Koenigsegg</h1> 
            <img src="resources\About\koenigsegg-ghost-logo.jpg" alt="Koenigsegg Jesko" width="100">
            <p>Koenigsegg Automotive AB is a Swedish manufacturer of high-performance sports cars, founded in 1994 by Christian von Koenigsegg. The company is known for its commitment to innovation, advanced engineering, and exceptional performance.</p>
        </section>
        </center>
        <div class="container">
        <section>
            <h2>Models</h2>
            <article>
                <h3>Koenigsegg Jesko</h3>
                
                <figure>
                    <img src="resources\Jesko\jesko.jpg" alt="Koenigsegg Jesko" width="600">
                    <figcaption>Koenigsegg Jesko - The Ultimate Performance Machine</figcaption>
                </figure>
                <p>The Jesko is named after Jesko von Koenigsegg, the father of the company founder. It features a 5.0-liter twin-turbo V8 engine producing up to 1,600 hp.</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h3>Koenigsegg Regera</h3>
                <figure>
                    <img src="resources\Regera\regera.jpg" alt="Koenigsegg Regera" width="600">
                    <figcaption>Koenigsegg Regera - A Revolutionary Hybrid Hypercar</figcaption>
                </figure>
                <p>The Regera combines a powerful V8 engine with an electric motor system, producing over 1,500 hp. It is designed for exceptional performance and luxury.</p>
            </article>
        </section>
        </div>
        <section>
            <h2>Technology</h2>
            <article>
                <h3>Light Speed Transmission</h3>
                <p>The Light Speed Transmission (LST) is a revolutionary 9-speed multi-clutch transmission designed to provide seamless power delivery and lightning-fast gear changes.</p>
            </article>
            <article>
                <h3>Triplex Suspension</h3>
                <p>Koenigsegg's Triplex Suspension system offers unparalleled stability and handling by integrating a third damper between the rear wheels.</p>
            </article>
        </section>
